      <p>
        While <strong>life expectancy Gini</strong> remains low (more equal), <strong>spending Gini</strong> reaches up to 0.70, revealing extreme disparities in investment.
      </p>
      <p>Global convergence in life expectancy is a success story: even with wildly different spending, the outcome gap is modest.</p>
      <p>Inequality in spending is deeply structural and barely improves over time, especially in raw dollar terms.</p>
      <p>PPP adjustments and GDP percentage offer more nuanced fairness metrics, but do not eliminate the underlying disparities.</p>

      <img src="/images/lorenz_curves_2014.png" alt="Lorenz Curves - 2014" class="rounded shadow-md my-6" />

